疫情导致学校停课，日本小学生在《我的世界》里“补办”了一场毕业典礼。
The outbreak caused schools to close, and Japanese schoolchildren made up for a graduation ceremony in "My World."
南回归线。
Tropic of Cancer.
趣闻。
Interesting news.
4天前。
Four days ago.
孩子的世界。
The world of children.
。
.
自3月2日正式停课至今，日本的中小学生们已经度过了有些难熬的两周。
Schoolchildren in Japan have had a rough time of two weeks since the March 2 official suspension.
受疫情影响，日本首相安倍晋三早前已宣布过，全国所有高中以下学校将一直停课到四月春假——这意味着无数中小学生的毕业典礼也会因此被跳过。
Affected by the outbreak, Japanese Prime Minister Shinzo Abe had earlier announced that all schools below high school would be closed until the spring break in April - meaning that graduation ceremonies for countless schoolchildren would also be skipped.
。
.
日本中小学大多实行三学期制，第一学期4月到7月，第二学期8月到12月，第三学期1月到3月。
Most Japanese primary and secondary schools operate on a three-semester system, with the first term from April to July, the second term from August to December and the third term from January to March.
而每年的三月下旬，正是各个学校举办毕业典礼的时间。
In late March of each year, it is the commencement date of each school.
日本人向来看重各式祭礼节日，象征着人生一个阶段结束的毕业典礼自然也不例外。
The Japanese have always valued all kinds of festivals, symbolizing the end of one stage of life graduation ceremony is no exception.
但受形势所迫，这些孩子似乎失去了隆重地与过去的自己告别的机会。
But the children seem to have lost the chance to say goodbye to their old self.
。
.
难道真的就没有任何补救方案了？长野县的一群小学生用实际行动回答了这个问题。
Is there really no remedy? A group of schoolchildren in Nagano County answered the question with practical actions.
。
.
这个月的14日，柏原周平，一位普通的日本父亲，在家中见证了自己孩子参加毕业典礼的一幕。
On the 14th of this month, an ordinary Japanese father witnessed the graduation of his child at his home.
。
.
对这个HUD感到眼熟是件再正常不过的事，因为这场毕业典礼确实就是在《我的世界》中举办的。
It's perfectly normal to be familiar with this HUD, because this graduation ceremony was really held in "My World."
柏原周平描述道，他的儿子和同学们花费了一天的时间建设场地，并随之在这个虚拟的世界中举办了毕业典礼。
His son and classmates spent a day building the site and then held graduation ceremonies in the virtual world, Mr. Buhara described.
。
.
全程没有校方参与的情况下，这群小学生一砖一瓦垒起自己想象中的礼堂，时而嬉笑打闹，时而合唱校歌——就像真正的毕业典礼那样。
Without school participation, the group of schoolchildren brick by brick built their own imaginary auditorium, sometimes laughing and laughing, sometimes singing the school anthem - just like a real graduation ceremony.
。
.
我们在形容开心的程度时常说“开心得像个孩子”，为什么要这样修辞？其实只要看到他们的笑脸，就会明白。
We often say "happy as a child" when we describe the level of happiness. Why do we use this rhetoric? Just look at their smiling faces and you will understand.
。
.
柏原周平将儿子的这份快乐分享到推特后不久，转发和点赞就破了万。
Bo Yuan Zhou Ping will share the joy of his son to Twitter soon after the forwarding and praise on the breaking million.
疫情笼罩的天空透出一缕光，嗅觉灵敏的各路媒体纷至沓来。
An outbreak of the sky revealed a ray of light, the smell of sensitive media came in.
讲述故事的同时，柏原周平还补充道，希望人们能以一种新视角来看待电子游戏。
As he narrates the story, he adds, he hopes people will see video games from a new perspective.
。
.
之所以会提出这种观点，是因为柏原周平本来就是个游戏迷。
The reason for this view is that he was originally a game fan.
他如今在长野县白马村经营着一家名为“木尘”的民宿，而他最喜欢的游戏是世嘉于上个世纪发行的《电脑战机》。
He now runs a house called "Wood Dust" in the village of White Horse in Nagano County, and his favorite game is Cyber Warplane, released in the last century.
。
.
去年年底时候，柏原周平曾发起过一次众筹，希望在自己的民宿中创建一个专供《电脑战机》玩家线下聚会的游戏中心。
At the end of last year, Mr. Zhou launched a crowd-funding campaign to create a video game center in his home for Internet gamers to meet offline.
。
.
这里会有宽敞的游戏场地，会有开阔的观众席位，会有很多珍稀的藏品（手办）。
There will be spacious playgrounds, there will be open spectator seats, and there will be many rare collections (hand-held).
人们会聚集在这里，并在享受游戏的同时成为朋友。
People congregate here and become friends while enjoying the game.
。
.
但《电脑战机》终究是款年事已高的游戏了，即便是在小圈子的支持下，柏原周平5千万日元的众筹目标最终也止步于1千1百万日元。
But Computer Fighter is an old game after all, and even with the support of a small circle, the crowd-funding target of Y50m for Buharahara ended up at Y11m.
在众筹界面，他曾介绍，《电脑战机》是一款不论什么性别、年龄、职业的玩家都能获得快乐的游戏。
In the crowd-funding interface, he said, "Computer Fighter" is a game in which players of all sexes, ages and professions can have fun.
。
.
可能正是因为有这样一位父亲，才能如此深刻地体会到儿子在操办这场毕业典礼中所收获的快乐。
Perhaps it was because of such a father that he was able to appreciate so deeply the joy of his son in running this graduation ceremony.
。
.
大人倾尽全力也很难做到的事，有时候对孩子来说似乎轻而易举。
It is difficult for adults to do what they can, and sometimes it seems easy for children.
。
.
